On Tue, 27 Jan 2009, John Baker wrote:

> I am trying to install an adapter to make a 1500 engine (case NOT 
drilled for an engine hanger bar) fit into a 1970 westy.  I need to 
remove the crank pulley to get to the oil pump cover top studs. Soooo, is 
removing and re-installing the crank pulley as easy as loosening the big 
bolt and removing then vice-versa for re-installation?  OR are there any 
special tools I need or other considerations when removing a crank 
